<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES70-5 - DISASSEMBLE -
        MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="13">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301123">Figure 23</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301123" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301123" filename="../figg13/g1301123.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 23. Mainshaft - Exploded View</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BAFFLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. OIL RING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. BEARING CUP</callout1>
                <callout1>5. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. INPUT SHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>7. 1ST SPEED GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>8. BEARING</callout1>
                <callout1>9. THRUST WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>10. SNAP RING</callout1>
                <callout1>11. SPLIT NEEDLE BEARING</callout1>
                <callout1>12. SPLIT WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>13. 2ND SPEED GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>14. 2ND-3RD SPEED SYNCHRONIZER</callout1>
                <callout1>15. 2ND-3RD SPEED CLUTCH GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>16. 3RD SPEED GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>17. 4TH GEAR SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>18. PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>19. 4TH SPEED GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>20. 4TH-5TH SPEED SYNCHRONIZER</callout1>
                <callout1>21. MAINSHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>22. 1ST-REVERSE CLUTCH GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>23. REVERSE GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>24. SPEEDOMETER GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>25. FLANGE OR END YOKE</callout1>
                <callout1>26. NUT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the mainshaft on a bench (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301124">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301124" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301124" filename="../figg13/g1301124.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Mainshaft on Bench</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable puller to remove the output bearing, thrust washer, and reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301125">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301125" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301125" filename="../figg13/g1301125.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Puller to Remove Output Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always wear safety glasses when pulling components off a shaft to protect your eyes from any
                        flying metal pieces.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Also remove the caged needle bearing and 1st-reverse clutch gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301126">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301126" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301126" filename="../figg13/g1301126.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Caged Needle Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable puller to remove the pocket bearing and 4th-5th speed synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301127">Figure 27</hotlnk>). Position the puller jaws behind the synchronizer clutch
                gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301127" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301127" filename="../figg13/g1301127.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Remove Pocket Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not pull on the synchronizer to remove the bearing. Doing so could damage the synchronizer
                        and cause shifting problems in the unit.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 4th speed gear snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301128">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301128" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301128" filename="../figg13/g1301128.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. 4th Speed Gear Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 4th speed gear and thrust washer from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301129">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301129" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301129" filename="../figg13/g1301129.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. 4th Speed Gear and Thrust Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable puller to remove 3rd speed gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301130">Figure 30</hotlnk>). Remove the spacer next. It is held in place by a pin.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301130" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301130" filename="../figg13/g1301130.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Remove 3rd Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear snap ring and synchronizer next (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301131">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301131" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301131" filename="../figg13/g1301131.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. 2nd-3rd Speed Clutch Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next, remove the 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear and 2nd speed gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301132">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301132" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301132" filename="../figg13/g1301132.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. 2nd Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two-piece thrust washer and caged needle bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301133">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301133" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301133" filename="../figg13/g1301133.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Two-Piece Thrust Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">These parts are not broken (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301134">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301134" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301134" filename="../figg13/g1301134.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Parts Not Broken</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring, 1st speed gear, thrust washer and caged needle bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301135">Figure 35</hotlnk>). Examine parts for wear or damage. Inspect mainshaft gear
                locks and synchronizer clutching teeth for excessive wear that could produce gear jumping. Clean all
                reusable components before reassembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301135" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301135" filename="../figg13/g1301135.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. 1st Speed Gear, Thrust Washer and Caged Needle Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
